<header class="b-header">
  <div class="b-header-wrap">
    <div class="b-logo-container">
      <a href="/i/logo-full.png" class="js-loupe"><img src="/i/logo-sm.png" width="256" height="256" alt="ColorSnapper Icon"></a>
      
      <div class="b-appstore b-appstore_header">
        <a href="<%= settings.product_mas_url %>" title="Get ColorSnapper from Mac App Store" class="b-appstore__btn">Available in the Mac App Store</a>
      </div>      
    </div>
    
    <div class="b-logo-text">
      <h1 class="b-logo">ColorSnapper</h1>
      <h2 class="b-tagline">The missing color picker for Mac OS X</h2>
      <p>ColorSnapper is an easy-to-use tool for quickly finding out the color of any pixel on the screen. It is activated via a system-wide hotkey, giving you a magnifying loupe to easily pick the pixel you need. The resulting color is copied to clipboard in a format of your preference.</p>
      <p class="b-buynow">
        <a href="<%= settings.product_mas_url %>" title="Buy ColorSnapper from Mac App Store" class="b-buynow__button">Buy from Mac App Store</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="b-donate">
  <div class="b-donate-wrap">
    <div class="b-donate__ill">
      <span class="b-donate__ill__plus">+</span>
    </div>
    <div class="b-donate__text">
      <h2>Help Japan&rsquo;s Earthquake and Pacific Tsunami victims</h2>
      <p><a href="http://itunes.apple.com/app/colorsnapper/id418176775?mt=12" title="ColorSnapper on the Mac App Store">Buy ColorSnapper</a> on Mac App Store to help Japan&rsquo;s earthquake and tsunami victims. We will donate 100% of this week’s proceeds directly to the <a href="http://www.redcross.org/" title="Red Cross">Red Cross</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="b-usage">
  <div class="b-usage-wrap">
    <ol>
      <li class="b-usage__item b-usage_pick">
        <h2>Point &amp; Pick</h2>
        <img src="/i/b-usage-1.png" alt="Point &amp; Pick">
      </li>
      <li class="b-usage__item b-usage_paste">
        <h2>Paste &amp; Use</h2>
        <img src="/i/b-usage-2.png" alt="Paste &amp; Use">
      </li>
      <li class="b-usage__item b-usage_select">
        <h2>Select &amp; Reuse</h2>
        <img src="/i/b-usage-3.png" alt="Select &amp; Reuse">
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="b-features">
  <div class="b-features-wrap">
    <div class="b-features__item b-features_shortcuts">
      <h2>Under your fingertips</h2>
      <img src="/i/b-features-1.png" alt="Under your fingertips">
      <p>ColorSnapper is always here when you want it to be. No matter which application you are using, just press the chosen combination of the keys and it’s here!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="b-features__item b-features_format">
      <h2>In the format you want</h2>
      <img src="/i/b-features-2.png" alt="In the format you want">
      <p>ColorSnapper formats the picked color in lots of handy formats no matter what are you working on: web-site, desktop or iOS application. You can do both! Just keep the ⌥ (Alt) key pressed when picking you color to store it in an alternative format.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="b-features__item">
      <h2>Pixel perfect...</h2>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_2" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_2.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_3" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_3.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_4" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_4.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_5" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_5.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_6" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_6.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_7" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_7.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_8" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_8.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__item b-slide__item_9" style="display: none">
        <img src="/i/b-slide__item_9.png" alt="Pixel perfect">
      </div>

      <div class="b-slide__slider">
        <div id="slider"></div>
      </div>
      <p>With ColorSnapper you can really see what&rsquo;s on your screen. With magnification from 2&times; till 9&times; you will see every aspect of your design. Really, just try it out and drag the slider!</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="b-store">
  <h2>ColorSnapper is available on the Mac App Store.</h2>
  
  <p class="b-buynow b-buynow_footer">
    <a href="<%= settings.product_mas_url %>" title="Buy ColorSnapper from Mac App Store" class="b-buynow__button">Buy from Mac App Store</a>
  </p>
  
  <p>Follow <a href="http://www.twitter.com/colorsnapper" title="ColorSnapper on Twitter" class="b-twitter-btn_sml">@colorsnapper</a> on twitter to get latest updates.</p>
</section>

